OL,3,CTreasury must fully fund public sector
OL,4,Ctax increase, insists Robison
OL,6,FThe Scottish Government has said the
OL,7,Fcost to the taxpayer if the increase
OL,8,Fis not funded north of the border
OL,9,Fwould be around #500 million, which is
OL,10,Fseparate to the #3.4 billion funding
OL,11,Fdue to Holyrood ministers next year.
OL,13,FIt is understood the amount of cash
OL,14,Fcoming from the Treasury will subject
OL,15,Fto negotiations between governments.
OL,17,FBut Ms Robison has urged the
OL,18,FChancellor to provide clarity on how
OL,19,Fmuch funding will be provided to
OL,20,FScotland to cover the cost of the tax
OL,21,Fincrease.
